Status report of Yi Tong Tse on 12/18/98

I generated a small bitstream of 96x80 resolution for testing.  When scaled
up to D1 resolution, the bitstream has an equivalent bit rate of about 15 Mbps.
It has an average of about 10 coefficients per 8x8 block.  Benchmark shows
that a 200 MHz C6x can decode at 500 macroblocks per second.  For D1 resolution
at 10 I/P frames per second, this is about 26 times of real time.

Figured out how to compile the code and run the simulator in big Endian mode.

Spent some time to study TI's IDCT assembly routine and tried to integrate it
with my code.  However, I found out that TI's IDCT assembly routine can only
work in little Endian mode.  It needs to be modified to support big Endian
before it can integrate with my code.  The IDCT result also has a scale factor
of 4 in it.

Obtained a more accurate cycle count of the VLD assembly routine:
    Overhead for function call: ~8
    VLD with single lookup: 10
    VLD with double lookup, short codeword: 13
    VLD with double loopup, long codeword: 19
The total VLD table size is about 8K bytes.

